50|$|<b>Macrocystis</b> is a monospecific genus of kelp (large brown algae). This genus {{contains}} {{the largest of}} all the phaeophyceae or brown algae. <b>Macrocystis</b> has pneumatocysts {{at the base of}} its blades. Sporophytes are perennial and the individual may live for up to three years; stipes/fronds within a whole individual undergo senescence, where each frond may persist for approximately 100 days. The genus is found widely in subtropical, temperate, and sub-Antarctic oceans of the Southern Hemisphere (e.g. Chile, New Zealand, Australia, Falkland Islands, Auckland Islands, etc.) and in the northeast Pacific from Baja California to Sitka, Alaska. <b>Macrocystis</b> is often a major component of temperate kelp forests.|$|E
